==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Syntonin
<hw>Syn"to*nin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Gr. <?/
stretched tight, intense.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A
proteid substance (acid albumin) formed from the albuminous matter of
muscle by the action of dilute acids; -- formerly called
<altname>musculin</altname>. See <cref>Acid albumin</cref>, under
<er>Albumin</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

